.TH "PVXFOLLOW" "1" "2026-03-01" "pvx" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pvxfollow \- Single-command sidechain helper
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pvxfollow
.SH DESCRIPTION
Auto-generated from built-in --help output.
.SH OPTIONS
.nf
usage: pvx follow [\-h] \-\-output OUTPUT
                  [\-\-emit {pitch_map,stretch_map,pitch_to_stretch}]
                  [\-\-backend {auto,pyin,acf}] [\-\-fmin FMIN] [\-\-fmax FMAX]
                  [\-\-frame\-length FRAME_LENGTH] [\-\-hop\-size HOP_SIZE]
                  [\-\-ratio\-reference {median,mean,first,hz}]
                  [\-\-reference\-hz REFERENCE_HZ] [\-\-ratio\-min RATIO_MIN]
                  [\-\-ratio\-max RATIO_MAX] [\-\-smooth\-frames SMOOTH_FRAMES]
                  [\-\-confidence\-floor CONFIDENCE_FLOOR]
                  [\-\-feature\-set {none,basic,advanced,all}]
                  [\-\-mfcc\-count MFCC_COUNT]
                  [\-\-stretch\-from {pitch_ratio,inv_pitch_ratio,f0_hz}]
                  [\-\-stretch\-scale STRETCH_SCALE] [\-\-stretch\-min STRETCH_MIN]
                  [\-\-stretch\-max STRETCH_MAX] [\-\-stretch STRETCH]
                  [\-\-pitch\-conf\-min PITCH_CONF_MIN]
                  [\-\-pitch\-lowconf\-mode {hold,unity,interp}]
                  [\-\-pitch\-map\-smooth\-ms PITCH_MAP_SMOOTH_MS]
                  [\-\-pitch\-map\-crossfade\-ms PITCH_MAP_CROSSFADE_MS]
                  [\-\-route EXPR] [\-\-overwrite] [\-\-quiet] [\-\-silent]
                  [\-\-example [NAME]]
                  guide target

Single\-command sidechain helper: track guide pitch/f0 and apply the resulting
control map to a target via `pvx voc \-\-control\-stdin`.

positional arguments:
  guide                 Guide/input A used for pitch tracking
  target                Target/input B to be processed by pvx voc

options:
  \-h, \-\-help            show this help message and exit
  \-\-output, \-\-out OUTPUT
                        Output audio path
  \-\-emit {pitch_map,stretch_map,pitch_to_stretch}
                        Control map emit mode for the guide track (default:
                        pitch_to_stretch)
  \-\-backend {auto,pyin,acf}
                        Pitch tracker backend
  \-\-fmin FMIN           Minimum tracked f0 in Hz
  \-\-fmax FMAX           Maximum tracked f0 in Hz
  \-\-frame\-length FRAME_LENGTH
                        Tracker frame length in samples
  \-\-hop\-size HOP_SIZE   Tracker hop size in samples
  \-\-ratio\-reference {median,mean,first,hz}
                        Reference mode for pitch_ratio derivation in tracking
  \-\-reference\-hz REFERENCE_HZ
                        Reference Hz when \-\-ratio\-reference hz
  \-\-ratio\-min RATIO_MIN
                        Minimum pitch_ratio clamp
  \-\-ratio\-max RATIO_MAX
                        Maximum pitch_ratio clamp
  \-\-smooth\-frames SMOOTH_FRAMES
                        Smoothing window in frames
  \-\-confidence\-floor CONFIDENCE_FLOOR
                        Minimum tracker confidence
  \-\-feature\-set {none,basic,advanced,all}
                        Feature columns emitted by pitch tracker (default:
                        all)
  \-\-mfcc\-count MFCC_COUNT
                        MFCC column count emitted by pitch tracker (default:
                        13)
  \-\-stretch\-from {pitch_ratio,inv_pitch_ratio,f0_hz}
                        Source for deriving stretch in stretch\-oriented emit
                        modes
  \-\-stretch\-scale STRETCH_SCALE
                        Scale factor for derived stretch track
  \-\-stretch\-min STRETCH_MIN
                        Lower clamp for derived stretch
  \-\-stretch\-max STRETCH_MAX
                        Upper clamp for derived stretch
  \-\-stretch STRETCH     Constant stretch value when \-\-emit pitch_map
  \-\-pitch\-conf\-min PITCH_CONF_MIN
                        Minimum accepted map confidence for pvx voc (default:
                        0.75)
  \-\-pitch\-lowconf\-mode {hold,unity,interp}
                        Low\-confidence handling mode in pvx voc (default:
                        hold)
  \-\-pitch\-map\-smooth\-ms PITCH_MAP_SMOOTH_MS
                        Additional map smoothing in pvx voc (milliseconds)
  \-\-pitch\-map\-crossfade\-ms PITCH_MAP_CROSSFADE_MS
                        Map segment crossfade in pvx voc (milliseconds,
                        default: 20)
  \-\-route EXPR          Optional pvx voc control route expression. Repeat to
                        chain. Example: \-\-route stretch=pitch_ratio \-\-route
                        pitch_ratio=const(1.0)
  \-\-overwrite           Overwrite existing output
  \-\-quiet               Reduce helper logs and hide progress bars
  \-\-silent              Suppress helper logs
  \-\-example [NAME]      Print follow example command(s) and exit. Use
                        `\-\-example` for basic or `\-\-example all` for the full
                        set.
.fi
